727601f-b.title: Queens: Northern Boulevard - 77th Street
727601f-b.text:
Northern Boulevard, north side, east and west of 77th Street
(extends northward between the two buildingsi In the foreground at
the side of J. Pack 's roadhouse of 1891 extended Trains Meadow Road,
which was discontinued in 1908 as a street. View number two look-
ing eastward shows the old Jackson Avenue before it was widened and
renamed.
March 1924
Views 1 and 2
Euogene L. Armbruster Collection

727602f-a.title: Queens: Northern Boulevard - 77th Street
727602f-a.text:
Northern Boulevard, south side, between 77th and 79th
treets, showing in the center of the view the home of F.D.
Richardson in 1873. J. Fowler was the owner in 1891. In 1920
it was the Jackson Weights Wommunity Club House. It is not
standing in 1938.
May 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
